text: Gmina Mysłakowice is a rural gmina (administrative district) in Jelenia Góra County, Lower Silesian Voivodeship, in south-western Poland. Its seat is the village of Mysłakowice, which is about southeast of Jelenia Góra and west of the regional capital Wrocław. The gmina covers an area of , and as of 2006 its total population is 9,990. ==Neighbouring gminas== Gmina Mysłakowice is bordered by the towns of Jelenia Góra and Kowary and the gminas of Janowice Wielkie, Kamienna Góra and Podgórzyn. ==Villages== The gmina contains the villages of Bukowiec, Dąbrowica, Gruszków, Karpniki, Kostrzyca, Krogulec, Łomnica, Mysłakowice, Strużnica and Wojanów. ==References== *Polish official population figures 2006 Category:Lower Silesian Voivodeship
